    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Here are some design ideas:\r\n1. People can make \"servers\" (groups of rooms from a central moderation team)\r\n2. People can assign \"roles\" (fine-grained access control set by the admin)\r\n3. People can search chat history (even if it is encrypted)\r\n\r\nStickers+Reactions, bots and other features are not necessary, but No1~No3 are the big ones.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "1. Tox has a work-in-progress protocol feature called NGC (new group chats) that could add moderation to groups. \r\n2. I'm not sure about grouping of groups - that can be done in UI in clients already, but having shared permissions would be an option (once 1. is implemented)\r\n3. This is entirely a client feature. Toxcore has no concept of history, it's purely a network library. qTox has encrypted chat history with search now.",
